subSubSection.paragraph:
DESCRIPTION: Body moderately large (TBL = 
2.21–2.80 mm
), broad, robust (PNW/TBL = 0.46–0.53), rounded, strongly contractile.

DISTRIBUTION: This species is very widespread throughout North America (fig. 379). Matthews (1887) reported this species (as
A. californicum
) from Guatemala , but this record most likely refers to a different species.
